For sure, the technologies that are now available bring to front a different set of questions than the past decade. While all have been studied and deliberated on, we've re-prioritized. 

So, I think I've mislead you by setting this up as a dichotomy. 
The "yes, and"s ought not to be pitted against the "sure, but"s. 
They do not describe two types of people.
One is not morally superior to the other because they call out problems. 
"Yes, and" is not just for the technologist excited about their line of work. 
It's an attitude that is essential to any dreamer.

